Package com.ansi.scilla.web.division.servlet

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DivisionCloseServlet  
    DivisionListServlet
    Returns a list of divisions -- because it's useful sometimes
    DivisionLookupServlet  
    DivisionServlet
    The url for HTTP DELETE will be of the form /division/<id> The url for HTTP GET will be one of: /division/list (retrieves everything) /division/<id> (filters division table by id) The url for adding a new record will be an HTTP POST to: /division/add with parameters in the JSON The url for update will be an HTTP POST to: /division/<id> with parameters in the JSON
    DivisionTypeAheadServlet
    This url searches the following address table fields for the search type ahead "term": name address 1 address 2 city zip and returns the following fields: id = address_id label = name:address 1:address 2:city:state:zip value = name The url for delete will return methodNotAllowed The url for post will return methodNotAllowed The url for get will be one of: /addressSearch?term= (returns all records) /addressSearch?term=<searchTerm> (returns all records containing <searchTerm>) The servlet will return 404 Not Found if there is no "term=" found.

    UserDivisionServlet
